Hi David,

HKN (Eta Kappa Nu) offers free drop-in tutoring during the weekdays, 11AM-5PM in both 290 Cory and 345 Soda. If you're looking for private tutoring, you can also shoot me an email at hhe.brandon@hkn.eecs.berkeley.edu with your tutoring preferences and I can (hopefully) forward your request to potential private tutors in HKN.

----

In addition, UPE also has drop-in tutoring 10am-4pm weekdays in 346 Soda. In addition to that, part of our homework for CS 370 is to offer one-on-one tutoring, and there are plenty of tutors available for CS 61A. I believe there are weekly signups posted on the 61A piazza.

Hi David,

HKN (Eta Kappa Nu) offers free drop-in tutoring during the weekdays, 11AM-5PM in both 290 Cory and 345 Soda. If you're looking for private tutoring, you can also shoot me an email at hhe.brandon@hkn.eecs.berkeley.edu with your tutoring preferences and I can (hopefully) forward your request to potential private tutors in HKN.
Nicole McIntyre also has a list of private tutors organized by EE and CS course. You can contact her at nicolemcintyre@eecs.berkeley.edu or stop by 205 Cory.

I am looking for a tutor that is available Monday, Wednesday, or Friday. If anybody knows where I can get some one-on-one tutoring, please reply. I am willing to pay for these services. 

Thanks for reading this
